    "As in the rest of this study, we use the normalized Earth Mover's Distance to measure the distance between LLM and WVS answer distributions.",
    "Our initial expectations, before running the LLM experiments, were that LLM answers would be biased towards US ground-truth answers and away from 1990s (pre-mass internet) ground-truth, because of the supposedly heavy proportion of English-language web data in LLMs' training corpora.",
    "The methods presented in this section are a simple way to rule out such hypotheses.",
    "Several results can be obtained from this best-matching approach.",
